West Africa Monetary Union’s August Inflation Rate 3.5%

-- B y   E m i l y   B o w e r s
-- 
2011-09-23T12:13:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/west-africa-monetary-union-s-august-inflation-rate-3-5-.html
Inflation in West Africa’s eight-
member economic and monetary union was 3.5 percent in August
compared with 3.6 percent a month earlier, the Ouagadougou,
Burkina Faso-based organization said on its website today.  Ivory Coast , the biggest economy in the union, recorded the
highest inflation rate at 4.6 percent while Mali was the lowest
at 1.8 percent, the group said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  